message.content: The paper likely belongs to the arXiv CS sub-category "cs.CL" (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and question generation. Other likely sub-categories include "cs.IR" (Information Retrieval) as the paper discusses search engine queries and document retrieval, "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper proposes a new task for machine learning models, "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) as the paper uses an RNN-based encoder-decoder model, and "cs.DS" (Data Structures and Algorithms) as the paper deals with aggregating and distributing information from multiple sources.
